Love is in the air, and it is stylish… Presenting, some of this year’s most delightful Valentine’s Day campaigns.

Compiled by: @tofu_curryy 

#TheWordMagazine #ValentinesDay

For most women, leaving behind their favourite pieces when jetting off for a holiday is unfathomable. After all, what’s a little extra luggage weight compared to the existential crisis of wishing you’d brought *that* dress or *those* sexy heels?

The Word. unpacks the urge to fill your bags to the brim, and expert advice on how to deal with it.

Slide 1: English actor, author and columnist Dame Joan Henrietta Collins

Slide 9: (from top left)
Louis Vuitton Horizon 55, ₹3,40,000
Bric’s Andy Warhol Floral Print Trolley Bag, ₹1,19,000
Perquisite Aluminium Trolley in Champagne, ₹38,900
Gucci Large Jumbo GG Duffle Bag, price on request
Nappa Dori Steamer Check-In, ₹48,000

Words: @sharmameghna

latestPosts.caption:
Less than 24 hours ago, US President Donald Trump signed an executive order to reverse the US government's previous decision to stop using plastic straws.

This comes during a global effort to ban single-use plastic items, including straws.

The order will be effective immediately,  and Trump has banned federal agencies from buying paper straws or providing them within agency buildings.

"I don't think plastic is going to affect a shark very much, as they're munching their way through the ocean," said Trump.

According to Straws Turtle Island Restoration Network, over 390 million straws are used every day in the United States. These straws won't decompose for centuries.

latestPosts.caption:
A 2023 study by ResumeBuilder surveyed 1,344 hiring managers and found that 74% believed Gen Z to be the most challenging generation to work with. The reasons cited include frequent job-hopping (39%) and a perceived sense of entitlement (34%). 

But is it fair to write an entire generation off?

Many employers also perceive Gen Z’s openness about mental health struggles as a lack of resilience or an unwillingness to ‘toughen up’. However, Gen Z’s advocacy for mental health is reshaping how organisations approach employee well-being. In the past few years, many conglomerates have let go of outdated workplace norms and introduced a more supportive, inclusive, and flexible work culture.

Words: @sharmameghna

#TheWordMagazine #TheWordCulture #GenZ #MentalHealth

Here’s a quick recap of the The Word. Magazine x Bobbi Brown India beauty-meets-wellness lunch held in Mumbai recently. (@thewordmagazine @bobbibrownindia)

Friends of The Word. came together to experience a one-of-a-kind experience focused on inner and outer well-being. 

Actor and Bobbi Brown India brand ambassador Tara Sutaria (@tarasutaria) along with The Word. Editor-In-Chief, Nandini Bhalla (@nandinibhalla), led the conversation around beauty as the guests shared personal stories of confidence and inner glow. 

The wholesome chat concluded with a sound-healing session, allowing everyone to channel calming energies and transcend into a zen mode. 

During the course of the afternoon, the guests were also acquainted with Bobbi Brown’s Vitamin Enriched range that’s packed with skin-loving nutrients and lends a luminous glow.
